page.title: 01Wybunbury Village and Area
page.content:
Recently, the village of Wybunbury has increased in size, due to private housing development, which has now finished.No further plans are at present under consideration.
The neighbouring village of Hough is however expanding, and there are to be about 250 new dwellings built.
Wybunbury is of linear development along the B5071. The main development of the village was of houses built mainly during the Georgian period, with more rapid growth during the Victorian era due to the proximity of Crewe railway works.Thus, the architecture of the village is a mixture of Elizabethan, Georgian, Victorian and modern (1980-1985) design.A new, modern-style Church has recently been completed.
